node.text: I've shared a few of my Auntie Bug's recipes and I'm so happy that we finally got to spend some time in the kitchen together! I've heard so much about her version of Bananas Foster and it was AMAZING (not to mention Andrew's new favorite dessert) ✨ She also showed us how to make her simple caramel sauce which was also great on ice cream. They're quick, easy, and SO delicious - you guys HAVE to try these! Thanks so much for joining us live to make our Rosé sangria! We had so much fun and hope you love it! Listing the recipe here again! 🥂💗🍓

What You’ll Need:
• The Exquisite Collection Côtes de Provence Rosé (available @aldiusa )
• Lemon Simple Syrup (1 cup lemon juice, 1 cup sugar, and zest of 2 lemons)
• Juice of 1/2 Orange
• Orange sliced
• Lemon sliced
• Raspberries
• Strawberries

Making one of my favorite summer cocktails with @peaches.la_ 🍑 Cheers! 

Recipe: 
- A couple ripe, quality peaches sliced 
- 1 bottle white wine of choice (I personally love pinot grigio for this, but anything works!) 
- Purée of one peeled peach (blended with a little water) 
- 1 cup pineapple juice 
- 3 oz. brandy
- 2 oz. triple sec 
- 2 oz. simple syrup 

Stir, refrigerate for at least 5 hours and serve. Enjoy! 🍹

.

node.text:
HAPPY WEEKEND ☀️🥂 Here are a few of my favorite quick and easy summer dishes. I have reels on each, hope you enjoy! Which one are you making first!? 🎉

SUMMER QUINOA & KALE SALAD 🥬🍑🤍 Stop what you’re doing and make this delicious, nutrient-packed, refreshing salad! It’s filled with so many great ingredients including some quinoa for extra protein, pomegranate seeds and sautéed butternut squash. It’s light yet filling and perfect for a summer side dish (or if you’re like us, a huge serving for dinner). 

SPICY LEMON SHRIMP PASTA 🌶🍋🍤 This is the perfect summer dinner in my opinion! It’s quick, easy, and packed with heat and lots of flavor 🔥 I love it for a simple weeknight meal. This just became one of Andrew’s new favorites, you’ve got to try it! 

WATERMELON MINT SALAD 🍉🍃☀️ The perfect easy, light and refreshing Memorial Day weekend salad! It’s bright, colorful and filled with so much flavor. I love that it only takes a few minutes to throw together and it’s sure to be a hit with everyone!

BURRATA & FIG BITES 💕 These have been my favorite appetizer to make lately and they’re great for the holiday season. They’re also one of the easiest “dishes” to make! Love these little bites of happiness. 

MANGO GRILLED COD 🥭 🐠 🌶
SO ready for some summer recipes! This grilled cod is the perfect dinner - it’s light, vibrant and has just the right amount of heat from the mango garnish. The best part? How simple it is! 
.

UNCONVENTIONAL PEACH PANZANELLA 🥖🥬🍑 We have been OBSESSED with this seasonal salad lately. I know it’s not your traditional panzanella but it’s also delicious! Seasonal peaches, sweet cherry tomatoes, creamy burrata and crispy bread pieces - what more could you want!? The acidity from the balsamic ties it all together and makes it the perfect summer salad that’s perfect for entertaining. Enjoy! 
What you’ll need: 
Mixed greens 
Toasted stale bread 
Peaches @peaches.la_ 🍑
Cherry tomatoes 
Red onion 
Burrata @eatalyla 🤍
Cucumbers
Fresh Basil 
Fresh Mint 
Dressing: 
Extra virgin olive oil 
White balsamic vinegar 
Honey 
Salt & pepper to taste 
.
.
.
.
.

FIG HONEY RICOTTA FLATBREAD 🍯🍷 The perfect quick & easy weeknight meal! I love the combination of figs, honey and ricotta and it makes me feel like it’s much fancier than an easy meal that was just thrown together. It can be ready in under 20 minutes! Enjoy 💗
What you’ll need: 
Naan (you can make your own but I purchased it) 
1 tbsp. extra virgin olive oil 
1 tbsp. good quality balsamic 
1/4 red onion
Ricotta cheese 
Honey 
Baby arugula 
Goat cheese, crumbled 
Fresh figs 
Balsamic glaze 
Thyme 
Salt & pepper to taste 
*combine olive oil, balsamic vinegar and onions and caramelize for about 7 minutes. Top flatbreads with ricotta/honey mixture, caramelized onions, baby arugula and goat cheese. Pop into the oven for about 10 minutes at 400 degrees or until golden brown. Drizzle with balsamic glaze, place sliced figs on top, garnish with thyme and finish with salt & pepper. 
.
.
.
.
.

NOT YOUR AVERAGE SHRIMP COCKTAIL 🍤🍅🥑🍋 This is the perfect summer appetizer with no need to turn on the stove! It’s my mom’s spin on a shrimp cocktail and when we tried it the other day Andrew said we HAD to share it. It’s so quick, easy and flavorful. Best part? All you have to do is chop, dice, toss and enjoy! 
What you’ll need: 
1 lb. cooked shrimp 
Juice of 2 lemons (zest of 1) 
Juice of 2 limes 
1 cup seeded cucumber, diced 
1 cup radish, diced 
1 cup celery, diced 
1/2 cup onion, diced (red, white or chives) 
1/2 cup cilantro, chopped 
1 jalapeño or Serrano, seeded and devained, finely diced 
2 avocados, cubed 
Salt & pepper to taste 
Dash of tabasco
16 oz. favorite cocktail sauce (you can also make your own) 
Optional - 1 tsp. horseradish 
Enjoy!
.
.
.
.
.

SPAGHETTI LIMONE 🍋 Making the OG @frankprisinzano Limone tonight because there’s truly nothing better! The simplicity of this dish is what makes it so special and following the method is what brings it all together. Along with my amazing mom and grandma, Frank and his delicious methods (not recipes) also inspired me to get into the kitchen more years ago. If you haven’t made this yet, stop reading and GET TO IT! 🔥🍷
What you’ll need: 
Spaghetti 
Lemons 
Grass fed butter 
Parmigiano Reggiano (very finely grated!!!) 
*Do not add any salt but make sure the pasta water is HEAVILY salted. Cook the pasta al dente - do not overcook. Don’t strain the pasta and use tongs to transfer it into a pot - no heat - combine ingredients and stir quickly. If needed add some more pasta water/butter as you go. Top with a mountain of very finely grated (soooo important) parmigiano reggiano and dig in! 
.

.

SPICY PINEAPPLE MARGARITA 🍹🍍🌶 No better way to celebrate National Tequila Day! 🥳🎉 It really brings the heat - the flavorful pineapple and lime balance it out perfectly. We’ll be drinking this one all summer long. Cheers! ❤️
What you’ll need: 
2 oz. tequila blanco 
1 oz. triple sec 
1/2 oz. agave 
Juice of 1 lime
3 jalapeño rounds (more or less depending on spice preference)
5 pineapple chunks 
1 oz. pineapple juice
Salt & tajin rim 
Jalapeño rounds for garnish
Enjoy!
